What is the "Emitter Bulb" setting?\
\

\f1\b0 This is an attempt to emulate an effect sporadically used in movies. Although most of the time you don't see this, but in a lot of promo pictures, you'll notice a little bulge of light around the emitter of a laser as it's first fired or at the base of a light saber handle. I thought there might be an interest in this effect, and it was easy to implement, so I threw it in. Keep it off if you don't like it. I usually do.\
\

\f0\b Is there a way to get a "lens flare" effect at one end of the laser?\

\f1\b0 \
No. Absolutely not.  Overuse is not a virtue. Lens flare should be used only in situations where a beam of coherent light (if such a thing could really exist) would cause a lens flare in a real camera, which is rarely. Besides, there are any number of tools out there that will add a simulated lens flare for you.\
\

\f0\b Will there be a Windows or Linux version of Crimson FX?\

\f1\b0 \
There is currently no plan to create a Windows version. If there is sufficient demand, we will investigate porting Crimson FX to another platform. We've leveraged a lot of really great Apple technologies in creating Crimson, however, and no other platform has them all, so that means a lot of additional code to write, or the  need to license third party libraries. If you want to see a version for another OS, drop us a line, but we're not promising anything.}